modules.description: Converts OCaml float values to their string representations using the Grisu3 algorithm, ensuring precision and performance. Operates on 64-bit floating-point numbers and produces human-readable decimal strings. Useful for high-performance logging, data serialization, and numerical output formatting where accuracy and speed are critical.

Provides functions to convert floating-point numbers to string representations using different formatting rules. Works with the built-in float type and produces human-readable decimal strings. Generates the shortest possible decimal representation, ECMA-compliant strings, and G-format outputs for numerical data.
